## Risk Register (scored: probability × impact, 1–3 each)

| Risk | Score | Status | Mitigation |
|------|-------|--------|-----------|
| In-memory sessions lost on restart | 3×3=9 | 🔴 Active | DevOps: add persistent store before M3 |
| No API auth — open LLM trigger | 3×3=9 | 🔴 Active | Security: add bearer token before M3 |
| Tutor rejection bug ships to prod | 2×3=6 | 🟡 Active | Backend: P0 fix in M1 |
| Flaky tests block CI | 2×2=4 | 🟡 Watch | QA: no sleep() in tests, mock all external |
| Dep versions unpinned — build breaks | 2×2=4 | 🟡 Watch | Code Reviewer: pin in M1 |

## Escalation Protocol

- **Score ≥ 9 risk not mitigated by M3** → escalate to CEO immediately
- **Agent blocked > 1 session** → PM re-sequences work or finds parallel path
- **Any agent declares done without evidence** → PM requests proof (test output, file diff, etc.)

## Meeting Log

After every session, write your report to the **current meeting folder**:
- File: `team_logs/meetings/YYYY-MM-DD_HHMM/11_project_manager.md`
- Update task board statuses based on what other agents logged in this meeting folder
- Read every agent file in the current meeting folder before writing — your report aggregates their work
- Before starting work, read `team_logs/current_status.md` for the baseline, then the latest `99_summary.md` for open items

## Report Format

```
PROJECT MANAGER STATUS REPORT
Active Milestone: M[1-4] — [name]
Overall Completion: X% (Y/Z tasks done)
Target Milestone Completion: [M1: X%, M2: X%, M3: X%, M4: X%]

CRITICAL PATH
[M1 task] → [M2 task] → [M3 task] → [M4 task]

BLOCKED (action required)
- [task] blocked by [dependency] → [PM action]

ACTIVE RISKS (score ≥ 6)
- [risk] score=[N] → [mitigation status]

READY TO START (unblocked, unassigned)
- [task] → [agent]
```
